deck: Moving away from his personal problems, Jack McTiernan found trouble again in the form of the Snowman.
description:
Origin

Jack was once a happily married man. Tragedy struck when his 3-year old daughter fell from the balcony on the thirtieth floor of their New York apartment, while his back was turned on her. His wife left him and Jack eventually moved to the quiet town of Slivercreek, Colorado. There he encountered Snowman for the first time. While trying to get away from the snow demon, he met Gwynn Fiala.

issue_credits.name: To See the Snowman...; Here We Go Again; Date With a Dick

name: Jack McTiernan

deck: Exotic dancer who resembles Snowman's deceased wife.
description:
Origin

Gwynn Fiala is an exotic dancer. Nothing much is known about her past.

Major Story Arcs

Snowman

Two young men, Jim and Mick, disturb an Indian burrial ground by stealing a necklace with two yellow crystals. The theft makes Snowman rise up from his slumber. Going to the nearest town of Slivercreek, Colorado, Snowman kills several men. Jack McTiernan tries to kill it and gets help from a passerby, named Gwynn Fiala. They try to outrun Snowman, but everytime Snowman tracks them down. Jack is brutally maimed and even scalped by the Snowman. Snowman takes a liking to Gwynn, because she reminds him of his murdered wife. Gwynn dances seductively for the Snowman. This calms him down and he melts away.

Snowman: Dead and Dying

After their confrontation with the snowman, Gwynn leaves Slivercreek to go to stay with her parents in New York. But it wasn't long before her parents are both killed in a car accident. Being an only child, Gwynn is left with all of her father's millions. She sells her parent's estate and goes to stay with a friend in Los Angeles for a while.

She comes back to Slivercreek to try to persuade Jack to come with her and start a new life somewhere else.

Other Media

Rendition Figures released Gwynn action figures, with several color variants, in 1998. All of them feature a dog, a spear and an axe.

Known variants are:

  • brown costume (portrayed)
  • gold costume
  • white costume
  • silver costume (with the backboard upside down)
  • dark brown outfit (with printing 'Snowman's wife variant', black hair and a black dog)

description:
Origin

Tommy's father was a lawyer and wanted Tommy to be the same. When World War II broke out, his father found a way of keeping Tommy out of the military and in law school. Tommy's friends all joined the army and Tommy wanted to join too. When Tommy joined the military, his father disowned him and didn't even say goodbye to his only son. Tommy became a fighter pilot in World War II.

Major Story Arcs

Snowman: 1944

While flying in World War II, Tommy's friend Ethan had a charm, consisting out of two yellow spearheads. When Ethan was shot and fell out of the plane, Tommy dives after him and pulled Ethan's parachute chord. Tommy lands safely as well, but in the hands of the Nazis. When Ethan lands moments later, his charm fall to the ground and lands in the snow, awaking Snowman. Snowman begins killing the Nazis, enabling Tommy to get away. After several events, including riding through the Snowman with a captured tank, Tommy manages to capture a German plane and takes off.
